title: Gainesville Buchholz pulls away from Fleming Island in second half to clinch district title
text:
Gainesville Buchholz pulls away from Fleming Island in second half to clinch district title 
Sat, Oct 24, 2015 @ 3:03 am 
3-7A 
BUCHHOLZ 31 
FLEMING ISLAND 21 
Star of the game: Gainesville Buchholz defensive back Marcus Clayton returned an interception 79 yards for a touchdown in the first half and recovered a fumble in the third quarter that led to the game-sealing score and the District 3-7A title for the Bobcats. 
Turning point: Trailing by four points midway through the third quarter, Buchholz (7-1, 3-0) drove 50 yards on 11 plays for the go-ahead touchdown. The ensuing kickoff was blooped to the Fleming Island 30, where the receiver couldn’t handle it. Clayton recovered and two plays later, receiver Barry Moore threw a 20-yard touchdown pass to fellow wideout Luke Whittemore for a 31-21 lead. 
On defense: Defensive backs Isaiah Walker and Keon Jackson and lineman Andrew Brennan had interceptions for the Golden Eagles, and teammate Ryan Birge added a pair of sacks. ... Trent Whittemore added an interception for Buchholz, and teammate Taylor Garrison was in on a pair of sacks and had two tipped passes. … Fleming Island (4-4, 2-2) had six three-and-out possessions on offense and forced five on defense. 
Fast facts: It was the Bobcats’ first district title in 11 years. … Golden Eagles running back Trey Sneed rushed for 96 of his 112 yards in the first half. Lee Goddard For the Times-Union
